column22: We started in 2013 as a faith-based rural program in Centreville, AL. In 2018 we added an Urban Track in Birmingham, AL. And in 2019 a consortium was formed with the University of Alabama at Birmingham. We are much more than a residency. We are a community. We live in the marginalized communities we serve; our patients are our neighbors. Our residents do it all, from delivering babies to point of care ultrasound to advocacy on The Hill to international medicine, and everything in between.
